Police have been allowed to continue detaining a suspect arrested over theft of Sh140 million from Dubai for 14 more days. Milimani principal magistrate BM Nzakyo allowed detectives to continue holding him to enable them complete investigations. Investigating officer Emmanuel Ng’etich who is attached to the DCI said the suspect George Maina who has been on the wanted police list for the last five months was arrested from his hideout in Mwihoko, Githurai 45, in Kiambu County. During the arrest Sh240,00 and tittle deeds were recovered in the house. Another suspect who fled Dubai after being linked to the theft has also been charged. Ng’etich said Rebecca Musau was arrested on July 3 at Namanga Border Control as she tried to cross to Tanzania. Click here for the latest political news 